ves.=C2=A0
Capitalism evolves.=C2=A0
It=E2=80=99s easy to think of capitalism as a static system that enables th=
e evolution of the goods and services available to humanity, but capitalism=
 itself evolves, too.=C2=A0
Consider the Industrial Revolution. Wonderful results. Just look at that GD=
P chart! But it was also brutal. Among many issues, children as young as fi=
ve or six worked twelve to sixteen hours a day, often seven days a week, in=
 conditions unsafe for workers of any age.
Today, it is still better to own the means of production than to operate th=
em, but the efforts of labor unions, journalists, regulators, and even prog=
ressive businesses responding to market forces have contributed to a vast i=
mprovement in worker=E2=80=99s conditions. Henry Ford, for example, impleme=
nted a five-day, 40-hour workweek in 1926 not out of benevolence, but to te=
st his theory that reducing hours would improve worker morale and productiv=
ity.=C2=A0
Or consider the way ambitious technology businesses are financed. Prior to =
the 1950s, in order to develop and scale a new technology, you=E2=80=99d ei=
ther need to have been rich enough to fund it yourself, convince a bank to =
give you a loan, or build inside of an existing company. That constrained w=
ho could create what and how. When Sherman Fairchild wrote a $1.4 million c=
heck to the =E2=80=9CTraitorous Eight=E2=80=9D to form Fairchild Semiconduc=
tor, a new funding model was born.=C2=A0
Adventure capital or liberation capital, now known as venture capital, igni=
ted the tech industry as we know it today. As Sebastian Mallaby writes in h=
is excellent book, The Power Law, =E2=80=9CBy freeing talent to convert ide=
as into products, and by marrying unconventional experiments with hard comm=
ercial targets, this distinctive form of finance fostered the business cult=
ure that made the Valley so fertile.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0
The exponential curves I included in I, Exponential [ https://substack.com/=
redirect/19d148b2-3685-4862-8c87-1bf1f2373a84?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T=
7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] wouldn=E2=80=99t have been possible=
 without capitalism, but they also wouldn=E2=80=99t have been possible with=
out the evolved form of capitalism that includes venture capital.=C2=A0
I don=E2=80=99t believe that we=E2=80=99ve reached the end of history or th=
e end of capitalism.=C2=A0
I think crypto can make capitalism more effective.=C2=A0
