Crypto=E2=80=99s ideal state is that it will make capitalism more efficient=
 and accelerate progress across industries. That=E2=80=99s civilizationally=
 valuable enough that people will pursue it through booms and busts.=C2=A0
This is actually happening. It=E2=80=99s cliche to talk about investing in =
infrastructure at this point in the cycle, but onchain infrastructure has m=
ade huge improvements over the past year.=C2=A0
Layer 2=E2=80=99s (L2) like Optimism, Base, Arbitrum, zkSync, and StarkNet =
are making blockspace cheaper. Innovations like account abstraction, Supers=
ends [ https://substack.com/redirect/6347fa0f-39f2-4f27-b7c0-85e0484bf298?j=
=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], embedd=
ed wallets, and multi-party computation give developers tools to create smo=
other user experiences while retaining crypto=E2=80=99s benefits. Stablecoi=
ns are becoming infrastructure, as highlighted by Visa=E2=80=99s announceme=
nt [ https://substack.com/redirect/1809c169-574c-4e50-af15-9372dbabddc1?j=
=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] that it=
=E2=80=99s using USDC on Solana to speed up merchant settlement. Stanford r=
esearchers even proposed an ERC-xR standard [ https://substack.com/redirect=
/9c7a5499-dd76-4885-9ea9-bfb7a5edbd67?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlN=
uaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] that would make certain transactions revers=
ible. I=E2=80=99ve spoken to a ton of smart teams working on correcting cry=
pto=E2=80=99s obvious shortcomings.=C2=A0
Progress on infrastructure despite low prices and slow activity is a sign t=
hat there are smart people who still believe enough in crypto=E2=80=99s ide=
al state to bet their careers on it. It=E2=80=99s also an acknowledgement t=
hat the average user isn=E2=80=99t going to want to make trade-offs: they=
=E2=80=99ll want the benefits of web3 with the convenience of web2. While I=
 don=E2=80=99t think mass adoption is important yet, it will be crucial at =
some point if crypto is going to reach its ideal state. Entrepreneurs will =
need to get unique value from building onchain. Businesses will need to tur=
n to crypto to finance their projects, and lenders will need to be there wi=
th capital seeking opportunity.=C2=A0
I think that this coming decade will see faster progress, and more economic=
 opportunity, than any previous decade. The wheels are in motion, and that =
will happen with crypto or without it. My hope, however, is that by bringin=
g more of the capitalist engine onchain, we=E2=80=99ll accelerate progress,=
 let wilder ideas flourish, and give more people ownership in the upside.=
=C2=A0
As everything decentralizes [ https://substack.com/redirect/0d0d6768-e9cd-4=
7bf-a505-53902605b514?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOs=
a8-6m8ExkRNpU ], crypto can push capitalism further towards the edges, dimi=
nishing the role of Coase=E2=80=99s firm to the benefit of individuals and =
entrepreneurs.=20
Capitalism is good. Capitalism evolves. And I think crypto has a role to pl=
ay in that evolution. With a valuable enough ideal state, it=E2=80=99s inev=
itable.=20
