ach that ideal state.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">By ideal state, I mean the imagi=
ned end goal or highest potential that technology could achieve if all the =
kinks were worked out and it was deployed ubiquitously.&#160;</p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;">Understanding the ideal state is maybe the most important thing t=
o do early in the life of a technology, because if that ideal state represe=
nts enough value to enough people, the kinks will be worked out and the tec=
hnology will be deployed ubiquitously.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, =
64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Boom and =
bust cycles for such technologies are useful noise. The booms are useful fo=
r attracting resources. The busts are useful for regrouping, fixing problem=
s, and mapping the next leg.&#160;&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, =
64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Through any m=
arket cycle, the promise of the ideal state acts like a magnet, attracting =
new researchers, entrepreneurs, and investors to improve upon the work of t=
hose who&#8217;ve failed to reach it. If you believe the ideal state is pos=
sible, then you chalk up previous failures to poor timing or implementation=
 and keep trying new approaches.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64=
); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>AI, AV, a=
nd AR/VR are three technologies that wandered through the desert burning bi=
llions of dollars for decades and now look to be breaking out. It&#8217;s c=
apitalism: if the opportunity is big enough </span><em>if it works</em><spa=
n>, ambitious people will continue to try to figure out </span><em>how to m=
ake it work.</em><span> These dreams can&#8217;t die, even if thousands of =
dreamers do on the way.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64);=
 font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Recently, there h=
ave been fresh calls that crypto is dead. Prices are down, activity is down=
, people are leaving. I get it. It&#8217;s been brutal, and even worse, bor=
ing. But I&#8217;m more convinced now, as of two weeks ago, that crypto is =
one of those dreams that can&#8217;t die.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(6=
4, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>=
