&#8217;ve spoken to a ton of smart teams working on correcting crypto&#8217=
;s obvious shortcomings.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64)=
; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Progress on infr=
astructure despite low prices and slow activity is a sign that there are sm=
art people who still believe enough in crypto&#8217;s ideal state to bet th=
eir careers on it. It&#8217;s also an acknowledgement that the average user=
 isn&#8217;t going to want to make trade-offs: they&#8217;ll want the benef=
its of web3 with the convenience of web2. While I don&#8217;t think mass ad=
option is important yet, it will be crucial at some point if crypto is goin=
g to reach its ideal state. Entrepreneurs will need to get unique value fro=
m building onchain. Businesses will need to turn to crypto to finance their=
 projects, and lenders will need to be there with capital seeking opportuni=
ty.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-heig=
ht: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">I think that this coming decade will see fas=
ter progress, and more economic opportunity, than any previous decade. The =
wheels are in motion, and that will happen with crypto or without it. My ho=
pe, however, is that by bringing more of the capitalist engine onchain, we&=
#8217;ll accelerate progress, let wilder ideas flourish, and give more peop=
le ownership in the upside.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); fo=
nt-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>As everything =
</span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/0d0d6768-e9cd-47bf-a505-539=
02605b514?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNp=
U" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">decent=
ralizes</a><span>, crypto can push capitalism further towards the edges, di=
minishing the role of Coase&#8217;s firm to the benefit of individuals and =
entrepreneurs. </span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16=
px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Capitalism is good. Capitalism =
evolves. And I think crypto has a role to play in that evolution. With a va=
luable enough ideal state, it&#8217;s inevitable. </p><div style=3D"font-si=
ze: 16px; line-height: 26px;"><hr style=3D"background: #e0e0e0; border: non=
